{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fe1d88ca-c803-4659-a733-2d24e3b6d7a9","content":"It's a straightforward change. In your project file, simply **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n\n<!-- After — just delete the line, or: -->\n<UseVSTest>false</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's it. With **MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0**, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner. Setting `UseVSTest` to `true` was opting *out* of it; removing that property opts you back in.\n\n### What changes at runtime\n\n| | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console` / `dotnet test` adapter | In-process test host |\n| CLI | `dotnet test` still works | Also supports `dotnet test` and direct exe run |\n| `.runsettings` | Fully supported | Supported, but some extensions use new config |\n\n### Things to verify after the switch\n\n1. **`dotnet test`** — run your tests and confirm they pass.\n2. **CI pipelines** — if you publish results (e.g., TRX), ensure `--logger trx` is still passed; it works the same way.\n3. **Custom `.runsettings`** — review for any VSTest-specific adapter settings that may need updating.\n4. **Code coverage / other extensions** — make sure any extra test infrastructure still works under the new platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"340e2190-c197-4bf4-af07-73e22d143aeb","outputTokens":354,"requestId":"67E7:449B3:29AC7C9:2DF7996:69FD3462"},"id":"a71a575e-467b-4e0d-aade-366ad3bd3dae","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:55:08.966Z","parentId":"868c3119-c731-4c4d-bac1-26db965db7db"}
